quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,133,"And vie with one another for pardon from your Lord, and for Paradise, the breadth of which is as the heaven and the earth, prepared for those who fear (or avoid) evil"
  3,134,"Those who give charity, both in prosperity and in adversity, for those who control their rage, and those who are forgiving towards mankind. Allah loves the good"
  3,135,"Those who when they do an evil, or wrong themselves, remember Allah, and ask forgiveness for their sins - and who forgives sins save Allah alone? - And do not knowingly repeat the wrong they did"
  3,136,"The reward for such is forgiveness from their Lord, and gardens beneath which rivers flow, dwelling therein for ever - an excellent reward for those who strive"
  3,137,"Systems have passed away before your time. Do travel in the earth, and see what was the consequence of those who denied (the prophets or Allah´s guidance)"
  3,138,"This is an explanation unto men, and a guidance and a warning unto those who fear evil"
  3,139,"Do not give way nor grieve, for you shall overcome them if you but be faithful"
  3,140,"If a wound touches you, a similar wound has touched the others: these are only the vicissitudes of varying fortune which we bring in turn to mankind that Allah may know those who it is that believe, and may choose from you witnesses, for Allah loves not t"
  3,141,"And that Allah may prove those who believe, and blot out the disbelievers"
  3,142,"Did you think that you can enter Paradise without Allah testing those of you who fight (or strive) hard, and remain steadfast"
  3,143,"Verily, you used to long for death before you met it! Now you see it (and flinch)"
  3,144,"Mohammed is but a Messenger, messengers (the like of whom) have passed away before his time. What if he die or is killed, will you retreat upon your heels? He who retreats does no harm to Allah at all; but Allah will recompense the thankful"
  3,145,"It is not for any soul to die, save by Allah´s permission, written down for an appointed time; but he who wishes for the reward of this world We will give him of it, and he who wishes for the reward of the Hereafter We will give him of it, and We wi"
  3,146,"How many prophets, with them large numbers of devoted men, fought (in the cause of Allah)! They did not lose heart at what befell them in Allah´s way, nor did they weaken, nor did they demean themselves - Allah loves the steadfast"
  3,147,"And their word was only to say, \"Lord, forgive us our sins and wasted efforts; and make firm our footing, and help us against the faithless folk"
  3,148,"So Allah gave them the reward of this world, and also good reward in the Hereafter. Allah does love those whose deeds are good"
  3,149,"O you who believe! If you obey those who disbelieve, they will turn you back upon your heels, and you will retreat as losers"
  3,150,"Nay, Allah is your Protector; He is the best of helpers"
  3,151,"We will throw dread into the heart of those who disbelieve, for that they associate partners unto Allah, for which He has revealed no authority; but their resort is fire, and evil is the resort of the wrong-doers"
  3,152,"Allah has truly kept His promise, when you routed them by His permission, until you showed cowardice, and wrangled, and rebelled, after He had shown you what you loved (booty). Amongst you are those who love this world, and amongst you are those who love"